OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FJapan train driver sues    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fover 49 cents in docked    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fwages                      
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A Japanese train driver is suing his   
OL,6, employer after he was docked 56 yen    
OL,7, ($0.49; _0.36) in wages for causing a  
OL,8, brief delay to the country's famously  
OL,9, punctual rail system.                  
OL,11,FTrain company JR West fined the man    
OL,12,Fafter a work mix-up in June 2020 caused
OL,13,Fa one-minute delay to operations.      
OL,15,FIt argued that no labour had been      
OL,16,Fperformed during the stoppage.         
OL,18,FThe employee is seeking 2.2 million yen
OL,19,F($19,407; #14,347) in damages for      
OL,20,Fmental anguish caused by the ordeal.   
